moves.name: Ice Beam
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze the target.

moves.name: Hydro Pump
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Icy Wind
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the foe(s) Speed by 1.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Simple Beam
moves.desc: Causes the target's Ability to become Simple. Fails if the target's Ability is As One, Battle Bond, Comatose, Disguise, Gulp Missile, Ice Face, Multitype, Power Construct, RKS System, Schooling, Shields Down, Simple, Stance Change, Tera Shift, Truant, Zen Mode, or Zero to Hero.
moves.shortDesc: The target's Ability becomes Simple.

moves.name: Yawn
moves.desc: Causes the target to fall asleep at the end of the next turn. Fails when used if the target cannot fall asleep or if it already has a non-volatile status condition. At the end of the next turn, if the target is still active, does not have a non-volatile status condition, and can fall asleep, it falls asleep. If the target becomes affected, this effect cannot be prevented by Safeguard or a substitute, or by falling asleep and waking up during the effect.
moves.shortDesc: Puts the target to sleep after 1 turn.

moves.name: Psychic
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Flip Turn
moves.desc: If this move is successful and the user has not fainted, the user switches out even if it is trapped and is replaced immediately by a selected party member. The user does not switch out if there are no unfainted party members, or if the target switched out using an Eject Button or through the effect of the Emergency Exit or Wimp Out Abilities.
moves.shortDesc: User switches out after damaging the target.

moves.name: Water Pulse
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to confuse the target.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to confuse the target.

moves.name: Helping Hand
moves.desc: The power of the target's attack this turn is multiplied by 1.5 (this effect is stackable). Fails if there is no ally adjacent to the user or if the ally already moved this turn, but does not fail if the ally is using a two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: One adjacent ally's move power is 1.5x this turn.

moves.name: Disable
moves.desc: For 4 turns, the target's last move used becomes disabled. Fails if one of the target's moves is already disabled, if the target has not made a move, if the target no longer knows the move, or if the move was a Max or G-Max Move.
moves.shortDesc: For 4 turns, disables the target's last move used.

moves.name: Chilling Water
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Muddy Water
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to lower the target's accuracy by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to lower the foe(s) accuracy by 1.

moves.name: Psychic Noise
moves.desc: For 2 turns, the target is prevented from restoring any HP as long as it remains active. During the effect, healing and draining moves are unusable, and Abilities and items that grant healing will not heal the user. If an affected Pokemon uses Baton Pass, the replacement will remain unable to restore its HP. Pain Split and the Regenerator Ability are unaffected.
moves.shortDesc: For 2 turns, the target is prevented from healing.

moves.name: Clear Smog
moves.desc: Resets all of the target's stat stages to 0.
moves.shortDesc: Resets all of the target's stat stages to 0.

moves.name: Psych Up
moves.desc: The user copies all of the target's current stat stage changes.
moves.shortDesc: Copies the target's current stat stages.

moves.name: Taunt
moves.desc: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for its next three turns. Pokemon with the Oblivious Ability or protected by the Aroma Veil Ability are immune.
moves.shortDesc: Target can't use status moves its next 3 turns.

moves.name: Skill Swap
moves.desc: The user swaps its Ability with the target's Ability. Fails if either the user or the target's Ability is As One, Battle Bond, Comatose, Commander, Disguise, Embody Aspect, Hunger Switch, Ice Face, Illusion, Multitype, Neutralizing Gas, Poison Puppeteer, Power Construct, Protosynthesis, Quark Drive, RKS System, Schooling, Shields Down, Stance Change, Tera Shell, Tera Shift, Teraform Zero, Wonder Guard, Zen Mode, or Zero to Hero.
moves.shortDesc: The user and the target trade Abilities.

moves.name: Hypnosis
moves.desc: Causes the target to fall asleep.
moves.shortDesc: Causes the target to fall asleep.

moves.name: Rain Dance
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

moves.name: Endeavor
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target equal to (target's current HP - user's current HP). The target is unaffected if its current HP is less than or equal to the user's current HP.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's HP to the user's HP.

moves.name: Blizzard
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target. If the weather is Snow, this move does not check accuracy.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze foe(s). Can't miss in Snow.

moves.name: Nasty Plot
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk by 2.

moves.name: Soak
moves.desc: Causes the target to become a Water type. Fails if the target is an Arceus or a Silvally, if the target is already purely Water type, or if the target is Terastallized.
moves.shortDesc: Changes the target's type to Water.

moves.name: Grass Knot
moves.desc: This move's power is 20 if the target weighs less than 10 kg, 40 if less than 25 kg, 60 if less than 50 kg, 80 if less than 100 kg, 100 if less than 200 kg, and 120 if greater than or equal to 200 kg.
moves.shortDesc: More power the heavier the target.

moves.name: Wonder Room
moves.desc: For 5 turns, all active Pokemon have their Defense and Special Defense stats swapped. Stat stage changes are unaffected. If this move is used during the effect, the effect ends.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, all Defense and Sp. Def stats switch.

moves.name: Mud Shot
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower the target's Speed by 1.

moves.name: Vacuum Wave
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: Usually goes first.

moves.name: Aqua Jet
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: Usually goes first.

moves.name: Focus Blast
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Calm Mind
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack and Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk and Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Haze
moves.desc: Resets the stat stages of all active Pokemon to 0.
moves.shortDesc: Eliminates all stat changes.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Knock Off
moves.desc: If the target is holding an item that can be removed from it, ignoring the Sticky Hold Ability, this move's power is multiplied by 1.5. If the user has not fainted, the target loses its held item. This move cannot cause Pokemon with the Sticky Hold Ability to lose their held item or cause a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, a Silvally, a Zacian, or a Zamazenta to lose their Blue Orb, Red Orb, Griseous Orb, Plate, Drive, Memory, Rusted Sword, or Rusted Shield respectively. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: 1.5x damage if foe holds an item. Removes item.

moves.name: Ice Punch
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to freeze the target.

moves.name: Body Slam
moves.desc: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. Damage doubles and no accuracy check is done if the target has used Minimize while active.
moves.shortDesc: 30% chance to paralyze the target.

moves.name: Light Screen
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from special attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, special damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Liquidation
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1.

moves.name: Psyshock
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target based on its Defense instead of Special Defense.
moves.shortDesc: Damages target based on Defense, not Sp. Def.

moves.name: Aqua Tail
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Brick Break
moves.desc: If this attack does not miss, the effects of Reflect, Light Screen, and Aurora Veil end for the target's side of the field before damage is calculated.
moves.shortDesc: Destroys screens, unless the target is immune.

moves.name: Hyper Beam
moves.desc: If this move is successful, the user must recharge on the following turn and cannot select a move.
moves.shortDesc: User cannot move next turn.

moves.name: Power Gem
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Confuse Ray
moves.desc: Causes the target to become confused.
moves.shortDesc: Confuses the target.

moves.name: Shadow Claw
moves.desc: Has a higher chance for a critical hit.
moves.shortDesc: High critical hit ratio.

moves.name: Facade
moves.desc: Power doubles if the user is burned, paralyzed, or poisoned. The physical damage halving effect from the user's burn is ignored.
moves.shortDesc: Power doubles if user is burn/poison/paralyzed.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. Sound-based moves and Pokemon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
moves.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

moves.name: Whirlpool
moves.desc: Prevents the target from switching for four or five turns (seven turns if the user is holding Grip Claw). Causes damage to the target equal to 1/8 of its maximum HP (1/6 if the user is holding Binding Band), rounded down, at the end of each turn during effect. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass, Flip Turn, Parting Shot, Shed Tail, Teleport, U-turn, or Volt Switch. The effect ends if either the user or the target leaves the field, or if the target uses Mortal Spin, Rapid Spin, or Substitute successfully. This effect is not stackable or reset by using this or another binding move.
moves.shortDesc: Traps and damages the target for 4-5 turns.

moves.name: Future Sight
moves.desc: Deals damage two turns after this move is used. At the end of that turn, the damage is calculated at that time and dealt to the Pokemon at the position the target had when the move was used. If the user is no longer active at the time, damage is calculated based on the user's natural Special Attack stat, types, and level, with no boosts from its held item or Ability. Fails if this move or Doom Desire is already in effect for the target's position.
moves.shortDesc: Hits two turns after being used.

moves.name: Waterfall
moves.desc: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.
moves.shortDesc: 20% chance to make the target flinch.

moves.name: Trailblaze
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to raise the user's Speed by 1.

moves.name: Tail Whip
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the foe(s) Defense by 1.

abilities.name: Cloud Nine
abilities.desc: While this Pokemon is active, the effects of weather conditions are disabled.
abilities.shortDesc: While this Pokemon is active, the effects of weather conditions are disabled.

abilities.name: Swift Swim
abilities.desc: If Rain Dance is active, this Pokemon's Speed is doubled. This effect is prevented if this Pokemon is holding a Utility Umbrella.
abilities.shortDesc: If Rain Dance is active, this Pokemon's Speed is doubled.

abilities.name: Damp
abilities.desc: While this Pokemon is active, Explosion, Mind Blown, Misty Explosion, Self-Destruct, and the Aftermath Ability are prevented from having an effect.
abilities.shortDesc: Prevents Explosion/Mind Blown/Misty Explosion/Self-Destruct/Aftermath while active.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Focus Sash
items.desc: If holder's HP is full, will survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP. Single use.

items.name: Wide Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.1x.

items.name: Leftovers
items.desc: At the end of every turn, holder restores 1/16 of its max HP.

items.name: Choice Scarf
items.desc: Holder's Speed is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Grassy Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Grassy Terrain, raises holder's Defense by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Wise Glasses
items.desc: Holder's special attacks have 1.1x power.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Rindo Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Grass-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Assault Vest
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Def is 1.5x, but it can only select damaging moves.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Life Orb
items.desc: Holder's attacks do 1.3x damage, and it loses 1/10 its max HP after the attack.

items.name: Salac Berry
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Rocky Helmet
items.desc: If holder is hit by a contact move, the attacker loses 1/6 of its max HP.

items.name: Cell Battery
items.desc: Raises holder's Attack by 1 if hit by an Electric-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Quick Claw
items.desc: Each turn, holder has a 20% chance to move first in its priority bracket.

items.name: Mystic Water
items.desc: Holder's Water-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Eject Button
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, it immediately switches out to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Aguav Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpD Nature. Single use.

items.name: Light Clay
items.desc: Holder's use of Aurora Veil, Light Screen, or Reflect lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Ability Shield
items.desc: Holder's Ability cannot be changed by any effect.

items.name: Red Card
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, attacker is forced to switch to a random ally. Single use.

items.name: Expert Belt
items.desc: Holder's attacks that are super effective against the target do 1.2x damage.

items.name: Air Balloon
items.desc: Holder is immune to Ground-type attacks. Pops when holder is hit.

items.name: Adrenaline Orb
items.desc: Raises holder's Speed by 1 stage if it gets affected by Intimidate. Single use.

items.name: Weakness Policy
items.desc: If holder is hit super effectively, raises Attack, Sp. Atk by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Damp Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Rain Dance lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Starf Berry
items.desc: Raises a random stat by 2 when at 1/4 max HP or less (not acc/eva). Single use.

items.name: Splash Plate
items.desc: Holder's Water-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Water type.

items.name: Power Anklet
items.desc: Holder's Speed is halved. The Klutz Ability does not ignore this effect.

items.name: Twisted Spoon
items.desc: Holder's Psychic-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Blunder Policy
items.desc: If the holder misses due to accuracy, its Speed is raised by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Room Service
items.desc: If Trick Room is active, the holder's Speed is lowered by 1 stage. Single use.
